race.description: Rex Gorell Volkswagen Dual Choice Handicap
race.comment: STOLI BOLLI (12) is racing very well and can break through. He's placed in every run this time in behind some good types, just run down late at Flemington last time having beaten home She's An Artist two back. Shinn goes on and with any luck from the inside gate, he should be winning. PERSIAN SPIRIT (6) was a big price winner first up over Stolli Bolli, good again last time. Stays at 1200m again which is the little niggle but he's flying. SPIONE (13) resumes with a nice profile having gone 2/3 last time in. He's got upside and draws for the suck run. Respecting, especially if there's market support. NAVAL ACADEMY (11) struggled in the key lead up last time but likes wet ground which he should get and can improve.
